Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.90,English,,0,0,0,,Let's start class.\N{\rChinese}让我们开始上课。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.36,0:00:07.54,English,,0,0,0,,So last week we discussed the possibility\N{\rChinese}上周我们讨论了特朗普可能当选的情况。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.54,0:00:11.66,English,,0,0,0,,that Trump will become president\N{\rChinese}他将成为总统的可能性。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.66,0:00:13.76,English,,0,0,0,,and we discussed that\N{\rChinese}我们讨论了这一点
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.76,0:00:16.96,English,,0,0,0,,if he does become president in a\N{\rChinese}如果他真的连任期都能连任
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.96,0:00:21.62,English,,0,0,0,,second term there will be a very strong likelihood\N{\rChinese}那么很有可能会出现
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.62,0:00:25.14,English,,0,0,0,,that the United States will go to war with Iran.\N{\rChinese}美国将与伊朗开战。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.86,0:00:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,Now the question today is okay Trump wants to go to war\N{\rChinese}今天的问题是，特朗普想开战，但美国军方会同意吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.66,0:00:35.78,English,,0,0,0,,but will the US military agree?\N{\rChinese}but will the USmilitary agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.72,0:00:39.20,English,,0,0,0,,Ultimately it is the Pentagon that\N{\rChinese}最终是五角星才会执行这场战争并且
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.20,0:00:42.32,English,,0,0,0,,must implement this war and\N{\rChinese}必须由五角星来实施这场战争并且
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.32,0:00:45.00,English,,0,0,0,,if there is enough opposition from the military\N{\rChinese}如果军方有足够的反对，
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:46.36,English,,0,0,0,,then\N{\rChinese}然后
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.36,0:00:50.88,English,,0,0,0,,it is very hard for Trump to push a war.\N{\rChinese}于是特朗普发动战争很难。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.18,0:00:54.40,English,,0,0,0,,I want to make the argument today that\N{\rChinese}我想今天的论点是：特朗普将与伊朗开战。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.40,0:00:57.12,English,,0,0,0,,the military will go along with the war.\N{\rChinese}但如果军方有足够的反对，随后特朗普发动战争就很难。我想今天的论点是：军方会跟随这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.80,0:01:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,And it has to do with what happened in 2003, okay?\N{\rChinese}然后它要与2003年的事相连，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.94,0:01:04.92,English,,0,0,0,,So let's go back to the last time that\N{\rChinese}于是我们回到上一次的情形。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.92,0:01:06.86,English,,0,0,0,,America fought a major war.\N{\rChinese}美国发动了一场大规模战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.00,0:01:12.72,English,,0,0,0,,It was the 2003 invasion of Iraq called Operation Iraqi Freedom,\N{\rChinese}那是2003年入侵伊拉克的“伊拉克自由行动”。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.90,0:01:16.90,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So at that time, President George W.\N{\rChinese}好吧？那时乔治·W·布什总统……
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.02,0:01:18.82,English,,0,0,0,,Bush and his people,\N{\rChinese}布什和他的团队，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.52,0:01:20.94,English,,0,0,0,,Vice President Dick Cheney,\N{\rChinese}副总统迪克·钱尼，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.78,0:01:26.04,English,,0,0,0,,Secretary of Defense Donald Rumsfeld, and his deputy, Paul Wolfowitz, they want this war.\N{\rChinese}国防部长唐纳德·鲁姆斯韦德及其副手保罗·沃尔福维茨，他们都想发动这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.24,0:01:29.02,English,,0,0,0,,And they go to the Pentagon\N{\rChinese}他们去五角大楼
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.02,0:01:32.86,English,,0,0,0,,and say, listen, we want this war, give us a plan.\N{\rChinese}然后说，听着，我们想打这场战争，给我们一个计划。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.66,0:01:35.14,English,,0,0,0,,And the Pentagon,\N{\rChinese}五角大楼回应，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.54,0:01:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,the generals,\N{\rChinese}将军队，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.78,0:01:40.20,English,,0,0,0,,they're very experienced and conservative people.\N{\rChinese}他们是经验丰富且保守的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.52,0:01:42.22,English,,0,0,0,,And in general, when you fight a war,\N{\rChinese}总的来说，打仗时，
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.50,0:01:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,there are three things you must focus on, okay?\N{\rChinese}有三件事你必须关注，好的？
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.64,0:01:50.82,English,,0,0,0,,The first idea is mass force.\N{\rChinese}第一点是大规模兵力。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.48,0:01:57.82,English,,0,0,0,,Mass forces. When you fight a war, you want to overwhelm your enemy.\N{\rChinese}大规模兵力。打仗时，你要压倒敌人。
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.28,0:02:01.62,English,,0,0,0,,So when we say mass forces,\N{\rChinese}所以当我们说大规模兵力时，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.68,0:02:06.08,English,,0,0,0,,we basically mean infantry and armor.\N{\rChinese}我们基本指的是步兵和装甲。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.26,0:02:09.68,English,,0,0,0,,Most wars are fought using tanks and soldiers.\N{\rChinese}大多数战争都是用坦克和步兵作战。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.62,0:02:14.36,English,,0,0,0,,And the Iraq Army at\N{\rChinese}伊拉克军队当时有大约三十七万兵员，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.36,0:02:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,that time had about 370,000 soldiers,\N{\rChinese}好吧？总的来说，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.82,0:02:20.92,English,,0,0,0,,okay? And in general,\N{\rChinese}okay? And in general,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.92,0:02:23.60,English,,0,0,0,,the general rule of thumb when\N{\rChinese}当你入侵一个国家时，通用经验法则是
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.60,0:02:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,you invade a country is you want to have a three to one advantage,\N{\rChinese}你想要有三比一的优势，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.32,0:02:32.10,English,,0,0,0,,okay? The reason why is\N{\rChinese}原因是当你入侵一个国家时
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.10,0:02:34.24,English,,0,0,0,,when you invade an army, when\N{\rChinese}你需要占领领土并补给士兵。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.24,0:02:37.88,English,,0,0,0,,you invade a country you need to hold territory\N{\rChinese}好的？所以你需要推进，也要占领领土。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:39.92,English,,0,0,0,,and resupply your soldiers, okay?\N{\rChinese}并且补给部队并准备预备队。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.12,0:02:42.30,English,,0,0,0,,So you need to advance but\N{\rChinese}所以通用经验法则是：如果你入侵一个国家并想占领军队，
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.30,0:02:46.80,English,,0,0,0,,you also need to hold territory as well as resupply your troops\N{\rChinese}如果敌方有30万士兵，你需要约100万。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.80,0:02:50.14,English,,0,0,0,,and have reserves, okay? So the general rule of thumb is\N{\rChinese}这就是第一个原则。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.14,0:02:53.76,English,,0,0,0,,that if you're going to If your enemy has 300,000 soldiers, you need about a million.\N{\rChinese}第二个原则是……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.06,0:02:55.44,English,,0,0,0,,So that's the first principle.\N{\rChinese}你想避免被包围。
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.00,0:02:58.94,English,,0,0,0,,Second principle is the idea of\N{\rChinese}对你的士兵来说最糟糕的事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.94,0:03:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,you want to avoid encirclement.\N{\rChinese}如果他们被敌人包围，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.44,0:03:06.90,English,,0,0,0,,The worst thing that can happen to your soldiers\N{\rChinese}因为那样就无法自卫了。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.46,0:03:11.20,English,,0,0,0,,is if they become encircled by the enemy,\N{\rChinese}而且…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.36,0:03:13.62,English,,0,0,0,,because then it becomes impossible to defend yourself.\N{\rChinese}第三个想法是保护补给线。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.62,0:03:16.66,English,,0,0,0,,The third idea is\N{\rChinese}战争大部分其实就是后勤。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.66,0:03:20.02,English,,0,0,0,,protect supply lines.\N{\rChinese}你怎么获得燃料和
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:25.86,English,,0,0,0,,Most of war is actually just logistics.\N{\rChinese}武器从这里到那里？
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.24,0:03:29.20,English,,0,0,0,,How do you get oil and fuel\N{\rChinese}补给线。所以
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.20,0:03:31.60,English,,0,0,0,,and weapons from here to there?\N{\rChinese}这就是三个主要原则
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.32,0:03:37.18,English,,0,0,0,,Supply lines. These are the three major principles\N{\rChinese}那时你必须聚焦的就是战时的要点。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:40.44,English,,0,0,0,,that you must focus on when you fight a war.\N{\rChinese}于是当……
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.88,0:03:45.60,English,,0,0,0,,When the Bush government asked the Pentagon for a plan,\N{\rChinese}布什政府提出军事计划时，五角板向五角板求计。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.82,0:03:49.44,English,,0,0,0,,the Pentagon went to the drawing board and\N{\rChinese}五角板走到绘图板前，开始作画。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.44,0:03:53.20,English,,0,0,0,,said to invade Iraq properly\N{\rChinese}说要正式进攻伊拉克。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.20,0:03:56.14,English,,0,0,0,,we need about a million soldiers.\N{\rChinese}我们需要大约一百万人。
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.40,0:03:59.62,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好的？然后
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.62,0:04:02.36,English,,0,0,0,,Donald Rumsfeld, who\N{\rChinese}唐纳德·鲁姆斯韦德，谁
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.36,0:04:05.40,English,,0,0,0,,was Secretary of Defense, and his deputy Wolford said,\N{\rChinese}是国防部长，他的副手沃尔福德说，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.58,0:04:08.80,English,,0,0,0,,no we're gonna do it with less than million soldiers.\N{\rChinese}不，我们要用不到一百万人去做。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.28,0:04:12.64,English,,0,0,0,,Give us a plan with,\N{\rChinese}给我们一个计划，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.84,0:04:16.16,English,,0,0,0,,that requires less infantry.\N{\rChinese}那需要的步兵更少。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:18.84,English,,0,0,0,,And the Pentagon said, okay,\N{\rChinese}并且五角大楼说，好的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.10,0:04:22.26,English,,0,0,0,,well we shouldn't do this\N{\rChinese}好吧，我们不该这么做
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.26,0:04:24.26,English,,0,0,0,,but the most we can do is about 900,000.\N{\rChinese}但最多能做到九十万兵
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:28.04,English,,0,0,0,,And Wolford said, nope, go lower.\N{\rChinese}并且沃尔福德说，没错，降到更低。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.88,0:04:31.82,English,,0,0,0,,And eventually, Rumsfeld\N{\rChinese}最终，鲁姆斯费尔德
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.82,0:04:33.48,English,,0,0,0,,and Wolford said, I want,\N{\rChinese}并且沃尔福德说，我想，
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.50,0:04:36.96,English,,0,0,0,,we want you to fight this war with a hundred thousand troops.\N{\rChinese}我们想让你用十万兵去打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.92,0:04:40.60,English,,0,0,0,,130,000 troops. Okay?\N{\rChinese}130,000兵。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.84,0:04:45.28,English,,0,0,0,,The Pentagon said to Rumsfeld and Wolford, this is insane.\N{\rChinese}五角大楼对鲁姆斯费尔德和沃尔福德说：这太疯狂了。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.34,0:04:49.66,English,,0,0,0,,We will be outnumbered three to one when we fight this war.\N{\rChinese}我们打这场战争时，兵力将是三比一。
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.32,0:04:52.44,English,,0,0,0,,How are we going to avoid encirclement?\N{\rChinese}我们怎样才能避免包围？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.56,0:04:53.96,English,,0,0,0,,How are we going to amass forces?\N{\rChinese}我们怎样集结兵力？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.18,0:04:56.34,English,,0,0,0,,How will we protect supply lines?\N{\rChinese}我们怎样保护补给线？
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.30,0:05:01.14,English,,0,0,0,,And Rumsfeld and Wolford, who are not,\N{\rChinese}而鲁姆斯费尔德和沃尔福德，谁不是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.24,0:05:03.78,English,,0,0,0,,by the way, professional soldiers, they've never,\N{\rChinese}顺便说一句，专业士兵，他们从未曾…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.82,0:05:06.44,English,,0,0,0,,they've never really fought a war before, they're like,\N{\rChinese}他们以前从未曾真正打过一场战争，他们就像是，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.46,0:05:09.62,English,,0,0,0,,well we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because\N{\rChinese}好了，我们有这个理论，一个新的战争理论叫做冲击与震慑。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.62,0:05:11.56,English,,0,0,0,,we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to\N{\rChinese}而冲击与震慑的概念是
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.82,0:05:16.40,English,,0,0,0,,try to defend ourselves because\N{\rChinese}所有军队都是层级结构
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.40,0:05:20.00,English,,0,0,0,,we're going to try to defend ourselves\N{\rChinese}好的？你有指挥与控制。所以你有头部
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.00,0:05:23.46,English,,0,0,0,,because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves\N{\rChinese}然后你有身体，接着你有四肢
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves\N{\rChinese}腿。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.44,0:05:29.66,English,,0,0,0,,because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going to try to defend ourselves because\N{\rChinese}好吧，如果我们能去砍掉头部
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.66,0:05:31.78,English,,0,0,0,,we're going to try to defend ourselves because\N{\rChinese}然后整个军队就散了。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.78,0:05:34.58,English,,0,0,0,,we're going to try to defend ourselves because\N{\rChinese}而我们能做到这一点，是因为战争的本质已经改变。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.58,0:05:37.42,English,,0,0,0,,we're going to try to defend ourselves because we're going because\N{\rChinese}美国军方专注的是什么，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.42,0:05:39.64,English,,0,0,0,,the nature of war has changed.\N{\rChinese}给我们优势的三件事，或者说三件事，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.10,0:05:42.64,English,,0,0,0,,What the US military specializes in,\N{\rChinese}第一点是空中霸权。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.78,0:05:47.32,English,,0,0,0,,what gives us the advantage is three things, or three things, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们掌控天空，因为……
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.52,0:05:49.74,English,,0,0,0,,First is air supremacy.\N{\rChinese}我们拥有世界上最大的空中力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.56,0:05:54.84,English,,0,0,0,,We control the skies because\N{\rChinese}其次，
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.84,0:05:59.26,English,,0,0,0,,we have the greatest air force in the world, okay?\N{\rChinese}最重要的是技术全知。
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.48,0:06:03.10,English,,0,0,0,,But second, what's most important is technological\N{\rChinese}全知意味着知道一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.98,0:06:12.80,English,,0,0,0,,omniscience. Omniscience means to know everything.\N{\rChinese}全知意味着知道一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.08,0:06:15.92,English,,0,0,0,,We're god! The reason why is, listen,\N{\rChinese}我们是上帝。原因是，听着，
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.08,0:06:18.50,English,,0,0,0,,we have satellites that\N{\rChinese}我们拥有卫星，能看到地球上的一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.50,0:06:21.00,English,,0,0,0,,can see everything on the Earth.\N{\rChinese}我们拥有卫星，能看到地球上的一切。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.22,0:06:23.36,English,,0,0,0,,We have technology that\N{\rChinese}我们拥有技术，能够……
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.36,0:06:27.48,English,,0,0,0,,allows us to eavesdrop on all electronic communications.\N{\rChinese}让我们能窃听所有电子通信。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.44,0:06:31.08,English,,0,0,0,,When you talk on the phone, we can hear exactly what you're saying.\N{\rChinese}好的？打电话时我们能听到你说的每一句话。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.92,0:06:33.74,English,,0,0,0,,We know everything on the ground.\N{\rChinese}我们掌握地面的一切信息。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.90,0:06:37.06,English,,0,0,0,,That allows us to have the power of God.\N{\rChinese}那让我们拥有上帝之力，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.34,0:06:42.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? That's the second thing. The third thing is we have special forces.\N{\rChinese}第三点是我们有特种部队。
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.82,0:06:47.12,English,,0,0,0,,So special forces are soldiers\N{\rChinese}特种部队是进入敌方领土的士兵
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:50.30,English,,0,0,0,,who go into enemy territory\N{\rChinese}他们进入敌方领土
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.30,0:06:53.46,English,,0,0,0,,and they are able to target and\N{\rChinese}并能精准打击
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:57.72,English,,0,0,0,,direct air power against the enemy.\N{\rChinese}并将空中力量直接投向敌方
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.54,0:07:00.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And\N{\rChinese}好？我们美国，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.38,0:07:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,we America have the best special forces in the world.\N{\rChinese}拥有世界最强的特种部队。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.98,0:07:09.52,English,,0,0,0,,And so\N{\rChinese}于是，凭借这三点，
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:13.68,English,,0,0,0,,with these three things we have a new doctrine of war.\N{\rChinese}我们拥有全新的战争理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.84,0:07:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,We can fight war in a new way that's never been fought before\N{\rChinese}我们可以以全新的方式打仗，前所未有。
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.86,0:07:21.76,English,,0,0,0,,but which will guarantee that war will be quick,\N{\rChinese}这将确保战争迅速结束。
