Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.58,0:23:20.58,English,,0,0,0,,America is an empire.\N{\rChinese}在美国，有七万三千人在全球奔走，试图守护美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.86,0:23:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately, most Americans don't want to admit that.\N{\rChinese}在美国，有七万三千人在全球奔走，试图守护美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.34,0:23:30.58,English,,0,0,0,,Because being an empire means doing bad things to innocent people.\N{\rChinese}在美国，有七万三千人在全球奔走，试图守护美帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.88,0:23:33.78,English,,0,0,0,,And what Shaw and all allows...\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.78,0:23:38.78,English,,0,0,0,,What Shaw and all allows is for America to be an empire without the guilt of being an empire.\N{\rChinese}特种部队员数量增加了，
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.18,0:23:44.14,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You have special forces doing all the work necessary in order to maintain this empire\N{\rChinese}这确实改变了美国军队的本质。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.70,0:23:46.24,English,,0,0,0,,without people actually knowing.\N{\rChinese}于是，这对美国来说是件好事，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.46,0:23:48.00,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So Shaw and\N{\rChinese}现在一切都让美国能够
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.00,0:23:53.26,English,,0,0,0,,all is really a theory of empire as opposed to a theory of war.\N{\rChinese}一次性地在各处出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.48,0:23:57.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So does it make sense to you guys so far?\N{\rChinese}而你们永远看不到它们。
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.32,0:23:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Any questions so far?\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以，例如，例子是
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.96,0:24:03.76,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Okay.\N{\rChinese}当加达菲在2011年利比亚战争中被推翻时。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.06,0:24:19.48,English,,0,0,0,,So... Okay. So, Celine asked a great question.\N{\rChinese}好的？那是特种部队。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.04,0:24:22.22,English,,0,0,0,,Are there... There's more special forces.\N{\rChinese}但我们不知道，因为特种部队隐藏在背景里。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.38,0:24:25.62,English,,0,0,0,,Is it because there's more people who want to be special forces?\N{\rChinese}好的？对加达菲进行空中打击。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.74,0:24:28.44,English,,0,0,0,,Or is it because America needs more special forces?\N{\rChinese}所以，换句话说，Shaw和…的全部真正是，
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.54,0:24:30.58,English,,0,0,0,,The answer is both. Okay? So, again,\N{\rChinese}是它不只是战争理论而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.96,0:24:33.46,English,,0,0,0,,the... America...\N{\rChinese}is it's more than a theory of war.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.46,0:24:37.06,English,,0,0,0,,America... After the fall of the Soviet Union,\N{\rChinese}它最终是一种帝国理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.26,0:24:38.64,English,,0,0,0,,no longer had a peer competitor.\N{\rChinese}美国是一个帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.18,0:24:42.82,English,,0,0,0,,So the understanding of America is\N{\rChinese}但不幸的是，大多数美国人不想成为美国人。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.82,0:24:45.40,English,,0,0,0,,that from now on, they will have to fight rogue regimes.\N{\rChinese}他们也不愿意承认这一点。因为
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.94,0:24:48.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So small nations that\N{\rChinese}成为一个帝国意味着对无辩者做坏事。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.84,0:24:52.12,English,,0,0,0,,don't really listen to America, and\N{\rChinese}而“全能手枪”所允许的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.12,0:24:54.94,English,,0,0,0,,these nations have to be toppled very quickly.\N{\rChinese}让美国成为帝国而不负帝国之罪。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.14,0:24:57.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the examples would be Iraq,\N{\rChinese}好的？你们有特殊力量完成所有必要工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.08,0:25:00.00,English,,0,0,0,,Iran, North Korea.\N{\rChinese}以此维持帝国，人民却不知晓。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.08,0:25:01.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The axis of evil.\N{\rChinese}好的？那就，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.62,0:25:07.48,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So America started to shift its doctrine to shadow wars.\N{\rChinese}全能手枪实际上是一种帝国理论，而非战争理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.62,0:25:11.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Wars that you don't really see, but which\N{\rChinese}好的？到目前为止，你们觉得有道理吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.08,0:25:17.00,English,,0,0,0,,would be effective in toppling the regimes you don't like.\N{\rChinese}好的，至此还有问题吗？对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.10,0:25:19.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And so\N{\rChinese}好的，接着，塞利娜提出了一个很好的问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.34,0:25:22.42,English,,0,0,0,,a lot of the resources were shifted into special forces,\N{\rChinese}有吗，更多的特殊力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.54,0:25:27.08,English,,0,0,0,,and that allowed more people to enter special forces.\N{\rChinese}是因为有更多人想成为特种部队吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.06,0:25:30.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense?\N{\rChinese}还是因为美国需要更多特种部队？
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.32,0:25:33.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. All right. Any more questions before I move on?\N{\rChinese}答案是两者兼而已。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.92,0:25:37.78,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Now the question then is, all right,\N{\rChinese}美国，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.88,0:25:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,shock and awe, where does this come from?\N{\rChinese}在苏联解体后，再也没有了同等竞争者。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.10,0:25:46.68,English,,0,0,0,,It comes from one of the greatest\N{\rChinese}于是，美国的理解是。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.68,0:25:49.24,English,,0,0,0,,disasters for America called the Vietnam War.\N{\rChinese}从此以后，他们将要去打击流氓政权。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.58,0:25:53.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So from 1965 until 1973,\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是，小国们不太听美国，
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.74,0:25:58.88,English,,0,0,0,,there was a civil war in Vietnam between North Vietnam,\N{\rChinese}这些国家得很快被推翻。
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.04,0:26:01.72,English,,0,0,0,,which was communist, and South Vietnam.\N{\rChinese}好的？那么，例子就是伊拉克、伊朗、北韩。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.74,0:26:04.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the war started in Vietnam, which is basically a U.S.\N{\rChinese}好的？那就是邪恶轴线。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.70,0:26:07.42,English,,0,0,0,,controlled puppet state. Okay? And\N{\rChinese}Okay? The axis of evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.42,0:26:10.48,English,,0,0,0,,America sent soldiers from 1965\N{\rChinese}于是，美国开始把其战略转向影子战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.48,0:26:13.16,English,,0,0,0,,to 1973 to protect\N{\rChinese}好吧？你看不见的战争，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.16,0:26:17.52,English,,0,0,0,,South Vietnam from insurgents and rebels.\N{\rChinese}但能有效推翻
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.44,0:26:20.46,English,,0,0,0,,And at the height of this war,\N{\rChinese}你不喜欢的政权。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.80,0:26:23.74,English,,0,0,0,,three million U.S.\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.74,0:26:27.14,English,,0,0,0,,soldiers had to be deployed.\N{\rChinese}大量资源被转入特种部队。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.34,0:26:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay?\N{\rChinese}并且这让更多人加入特种部队。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.82,0:26:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,And at the height, in 1969,\N{\rChinese}好吧？这样说通吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.02,0:26:33.40,English,,0,0,0,,500,000 soldiers, U.S.\N{\rChinese}好。好了。还有别的问题吗？再继续吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.40,0:26:38.12,English,,0,0,0,,soldiers, were in country to fight against the rebels and the insurgents.\N{\rChinese}好了。现在，问题是，好吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.38,0:26:42.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? 58,000 U.S.\N{\rChinese}震惊与敬畏，这来自何处？
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.46,0:26:44.74,English,,0,0,0,,soldiers died in this war.\N{\rChinese}它来自其中一大事。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.20,0:26:49.38,English,,0,0,0,,Three million, at least three million,\N{\rChinese}灾难被称为越南战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.42,0:26:51.90,English,,0,0,0,,Vietnamese died in this war.\N{\rChinese}好吧？于是从1965到1973，
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.10,0:26:54.70,English,,0,0,0,,Two million of them were civilians,\N{\rChinese}越南发生了内战，北越是共产主义的。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.08,0:26:56.36,English,,0,0,0,,innocent civilians. Okay?\N{\rChinese}和南越，南越是美国控制的傀儡国。
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.56,0:27:03.04,English,,0,0,0,,Over 300,000 U.S.\N{\rChinese}美国派兵去南越。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.06,0:27:04.82,English,,0,0,0,,soldiers were wounded.\N{\rChinese}And America sentsoldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.02,0:27:09.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They went home without legs, without arms.\N{\rChinese}从1965年到1973年
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.64,0:27:12.06,English,,0,0,0,,And they were traumatized.\N{\rChinese}保卫南越免受叛军侵扰
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.58,0:27:17.38,English,,0,0,0,,And this was an extremely controversial war in America\N{\rChinese}在这场战争的高峰期
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.38,0:27:22.60,English,,0,0,0,,because they were trying to fight the war using standard military doctrine,\N{\rChinese}300万美军需要部署。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.92,0:27:25.98,English,,0,0,0,,mass forces. Right? So, the institute did something called a draft.\N{\rChinese}好的？在高峰期，1969年，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.22,0:27:29.42,English,,0,0,0,,So, if you were a young American, you had to go fight in this war in Vietnam.\N{\rChinese}50万美军，
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.80,0:27:32.20,English,,0,0,0,,But you didn't know why you had to go fight this war.\N{\rChinese}在该国驻军与叛军和叛乱作战。好的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.40,0:27:34.10,English,,0,0,0,,And chances are that\N{\rChinese}58,000名美军在此战中阵亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.10,0:27:37.92,English,,0,0,0,,you would either die or you would lose a body part in this war.\N{\rChinese}300万名美军在此战中阵亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.24,0:27:41.48,English,,0,0,0,,So, it became extremely unpopular in America.\N{\rChinese}至少有300万越南人死于此战。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.02,0:27:46.64,English,,0,0,0,,The other thing is that there were a lot of journalists in Vietnam during this time.\N{\rChinese}其中200万是平民，普通百姓。好的吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.74,0:27:52.54,English,,0,0,0,,And they were reporting on how America was killing Vietnamese for no reason.\N{\rChinese}超过30万美军受伤。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.68,0:27:56.78,English,,0,0,0,,So, the most famous of these journalists was the American journalist, Mr. Lee. And the most famous story is something called the My Lai Massacre where American soldiers\N{\rChinese}好的吗？他们回家时没了腿，没了手，且受了重创。
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.40,0:28:00.34,English,,0,0,0,,went into a Vietnamese village and killed everyone there.\N{\rChinese}而这场战争极具争议。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.48,0:28:02.16,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? 300 people, 400 people.\N{\rChinese}And this was an extremely controversial war
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.28,0:28:04.32,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And this was happening actually quite a lot.\N{\rChinese}在美国因为
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.74,0:28:07.86,English,,0,0,0,,So, there was widespread anger\N{\rChinese}他们试图用标准军事实战术、规模部队来作战，右吗？于是他们设立了所谓的征兵制。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.86,0:28:11.68,English,,0,0,0,,and protest in America at this time,\N{\rChinese}mass forces, right? So they instituted something called a draft.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.82,0:28:16.56,English,,0,0,0,,which ultimately forced America to withdraw in 1973.\N{\rChinese}如果你是个年轻的美国人，你就得去越南打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.52,0:28:19.60,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And...\N{\rChinese}但你不知道为什么要去打这场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.84,0:28:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,The U.S. military was very angry about this war.\N{\rChinese}很可能是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.82,0:28:32.64,English,,0,0,0,,Because the thing about generals is they don't like to lose wars.\N{\rChinese}你要么死在这场战争里，要么失去一肢体。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.40,0:28:35.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? When they fight wars,\N{\rChinese}于是在美国极为不受欢迎。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.46,0:28:38.48,English,,0,0,0,,they want to win at all costs.\N{\rChinese}另外还有很多记者。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.46,0:28:43.60,English,,0,0,0,,And they felt that they were betrayed by the country.\N{\rChinese}在越南的那段时间里。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.56,0:28:49.76,English,,0,0,0,,They were fighting hard to maintain the American empire,\N{\rChinese}他们在报道美国如何无缘无故地杀死越南人。
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.02,0:28:51.88,English,,0,0,0,,to fight against communism.\N{\rChinese}was killing Vietnamese for no reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.14,0:28:53.82,English,,0,0,0,,And this was bringing the U.S.\N{\rChinese}于是最著名的故事是马莱大屠杀
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.82,0:28:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,military to a standstill. Okay? They're fighting to maintain wealth, power, and prestige to America.\N{\rChinese}美国士兵闯进越南村庄
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.78,0:29:00.28,English,,0,0,0,,But the American people, the American politicians,\N{\rChinese}全村人被杀光
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.70,0:29:02.36,English,,0,0,0,,the American democracy republic,\N{\rChinese}好的？300人，400人。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.66,0:29:06.08,English,,0,0,0,,refused to make the necessary sacrifices\N{\rChinese}好的？而且这件事实际上相当多。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.08,0:29:09.42,English,,0,0,0,,in order to maintain this empire.\N{\rChinese}于是广泛的愤怒出现。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.04,0:29:15.92,English,,0,0,0,,And so, many American generals felt betrayed by what happened in Vietnam.\N{\rChinese}并在此时在美国示威
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.46,0:29:20.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Now, there's a very famous incident during this war called the Pentagon Papers.\N{\rChinese}最终迫使美国于1973年撤军
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.02,0:29:25.38,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? In 1971,\N{\rChinese}好？
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.76,0:29:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,a group of\N{\rChinese}美国
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.14,0:29:33.16,English,,0,0,0,,American analysts, okay, they were,\N{\rChinese}军方对这场战争非常激动
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.18,0:29:36.04,English,,0,0,0,,these were military analysts working in the military.\N{\rChinese}因为将军的事，军方不喜欢输战
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.26,0:29:39.52,English,,0,0,0,,They secretly got together and they tried to compose\N{\rChinese}好？他们打仗时，想要全胜无误
