Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.32,0:29:44.78,English,,0,0,0,,And this was called the Pentagon Papers.\N{\rChinese}And they felt that they were betrayed by the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.02,0:29:47.04,English,,0,0,0,,This was meant to be classified.\N{\rChinese}他们奋战不息
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.50,0:29:51.00,English,,0,0,0,,This was not meant to be read by the public.\N{\rChinese}以维持美帝国，抗击共主义。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.00,0:29:53.74,English,,0,0,0,,But one of them, Daniel Ellsberg,\N{\rChinese}这为美国带来财富、力量与荣光。
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.96,0:29:57.06,English,,0,0,0,,linked it to the newspapers, Washington Post\N{\rChinese}但美国人民、美国政客们、
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.06,0:29:58.90,English,,0,0,0,,and New York Times, and they published it.\N{\rChinese}美国民主、共和国，
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.14,0:30:02.66,English,,0,0,0,,And people were angry by the Pentagon Papers\N{\rChinese}却不愿作必要的牺
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.66,0:30:05.32,English,,0,0,0,,because what the Pentagon Papers said is, one,\N{\rChinese}为维持此帝国而行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.54,0:30:10.64,English,,0,0,0,,America has been secretly fighting this war for a long time,\N{\rChinese}于是如此。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.80,0:30:14.24,English,,0,0,0,,okay? So many presidents,\N{\rChinese}许多美军将领感到越战中所发生的事让他们觉得被背叛。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.34,0:30:17.12,English,,0,0,0,,including Eisenhower, Kennedy, and\N{\rChinese}好的？这场战争里有个非常著名的事件叫做《五角大楼文件》。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.12,0:30:20.98,English,,0,0,0,,Lyndon Johnson, were expanding this war without any reason.\N{\rChinese}好的？1971年。
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.00,0:30:24.02,English,,0,0,0,,Without public approval, without congressional approval, okay?\N{\rChinese}1971年，
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.16,0:30:26.20,English,,0,0,0,,So there was a lot of deception, that's the first thing.\N{\rChinese}一组美国分析师
