Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.66,0:38:36.94,English,,0,0,0,,Shock and awe is fine. Okay?\N{\rChinese}震撼与惊叹还行。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.68,0:38:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,But our next class, we'll discuss Iran.\N{\rChinese}但我们的下一节课，我们会讨论伊朗。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.40,0:38:43.00,English,,0,0,0,,And Iran is not a desert.\N{\rChinese}伊朗不是沙漠。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.06,0:38:46.06,English,,0,0,0,,It's mountains. Okay? And I'll show you that shock and awe\N{\rChinese}它是山地。好吧？我会给你展示震撼与惊叹。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.70,0:38:48.14,English,,0,0,0,,is not gonna work in Iran.\N{\rChinese}在伊朗不奏效。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.38,0:38:49.80,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But that's next class. Okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧？但那是下一节课。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.84,0:38:52.20,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? All right.\N{\rChinese}那有道理吗？好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.56,0:38:56.28,English,,0,0,0,,Any more questions? In Iraq,\N{\rChinese}还有问题吗？在伊拉克，
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.52,0:39:00.64,English,,0,0,0,,after America had seen Saddam Hussein,\N{\rChinese}在美国看到萨达姆·侯赛因之后，
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.02,0:39:04.54,English,,0,0,0,,there was still a lot of fighting after they won.\N{\rChinese}他们赢得胜利后仍有大量战斗
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.72,0:39:06.32,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. They couldn't control it.\N{\rChinese}是的。他们没能控制住它。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.60,0:39:08.74,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So shock and awe is in a desert\N{\rChinese}是的。所以震撼与敬畏在沙漠中。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.38,0:39:11.20,English,,0,0,0,,in the middle of the country.\N{\rChinese}在国中间。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.46,0:39:14.76,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay. So Jack makes a great point, which is, okay, yeah,\N{\rChinese}是的，好。于是杰克提出了一个很好的点，嗯，好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.92,0:39:17.44,English,,0,0,0,,but most people would say\N{\rChinese}但大多数人会说
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.04,0:39:22.50,English,,0,0,0,,that America lost the Iraq war because of the insurgency, right?\N{\rChinese}美国因叛乱而输掉伊拉克战争，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.84,0:39:25.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. So, okay.\N{\rChinese}好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.02,0:39:27.24,English,,0,0,0,,That's a great point. Okay?\N{\rChinese}那是个好点。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.30,0:39:29.54,English,,0,0,0,,You can make the point that America, for the past 20 years,\N{\rChinese}你可以说，过去二十年里，美国在伊拉克和阿富汗的战争中都输了。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.60,0:39:32.48,English,,0,0,0,,have lost all wars in Iraq and Afghanistan because\N{\rChinese}have lost all wars in Iraq and Afghanistan because
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.48,0:39:34.70,English,,0,0,0,,they have not been able to control the insurgency.\N{\rChinese}他们未能控制叛乱。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.90,0:39:38.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But the problem with this is that\N{\rChinese}好吧？但问题在于……
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.02,0:39:42.38,English,,0,0,0,,shock and awe, it's not designed to stabilize countries.\N{\rChinese}震撼与惊叹并非用来稳定国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.38,0:39:46.68,English,,0,0,0,,Shock and awe is meant to topple and destroy countries.\N{\rChinese}震撼与惊叹的目的在于推翻并摧毁国家。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.72,0:39:50.70,English,,0,0,0,,Do you understand? And so the argument can be made\N{\rChinese}你明白了吗？于是可以这样论证：
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.70,0:39:53.44,English,,0,0,0,,that the real intention of shock and awe is to make sure\N{\rChinese}震撼与惊叹的真正意图是确保
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.44,0:39:58.74,English,,0,0,0,,that no power in the Middle East can arise to challenge America's supremacy.\N{\rChinese}那时，中东没有任何力量能崛起挑战美国的霸权。
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.80,0:40:02.82,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So yeah, in Iraq,\N{\rChinese}好吧？所以，嗯，在伊拉克，
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.20,0:40:06.28,English,,0,0,0,,the insurgents ultimately won,\N{\rChinese}叛乱者最终赢了。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.16,0:40:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,but is Iraq a functional state?\N{\rChinese}但伊拉克是一个功能性国家吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.76,0:40:12.36,English,,0,0,0,,And the answer is no, right? Is Libya a functional state?\N{\rChinese}答案是没有，对吗？利比亚是一个功能性国家吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.38,0:40:15.12,English,,0,0,0,,No. There's still a civil war going on in Syria.\N{\rChinese}不。叙利亚仍在进行内战。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.32,0:40:18.02,English,,0,0,0,,All right? So, but that's a great point.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，这点很重要。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.38,0:40:22.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And it comes down to what is the ultimately,\N{\rChinese}好吧？归根结底，究竟是怎样的？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.22,0:40:26.48,English,,0,0,0,,what is the ultimate design and intention of the empire?\N{\rChinese}究竟帝国的设计与意图是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.02,0:40:30.80,English,,0,0,0,,Is it to replace regimes or is it to destroy countries?\N{\rChinese}是要更换政权还是要消灭国家？
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.12,0:40:35.16,English,,0,0,0,,And you make the argument that shock and awe is really designed to destroy countries\N{\rChinese}你可以说震撼与惊叹的手段确实是为了消灭国家
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.16,0:40:39.34,English,,0,0,0,,and not to replace regimes.\N{\rChinese}而不是更换政权。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.54,0:40:41.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Does that make sense? Okay.\N{\rChinese}好的？那有道理吗？好的。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.38,0:40:45.32,English,,0,0,0,,So, what's important to understand is that\N{\rChinese}所以，重要的是要理解的是
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.90,0:40:50.86,English,,0,0,0,,one of the theories of the invasion of Iraq is to bring democracy to the country.\N{\rChinese}其中一个关于伊拉克入侵的理论是把民主带到该国。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.72,0:40:54.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? But the problem with that\N{\rChinese}好的？但问题在于
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.64,0:40:58.10,English,,0,0,0,,is, from the start, they did everything wrong.\N{\rChinese}从一开始他们就做错了所有事。
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.46,0:41:00.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So first thing is,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以第一件事是，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.74,0:41:04.70,English,,0,0,0,,they really didn't have enough soldiers to maintain peace, right, in the country.\N{\rChinese}他们真的没有足够的士兵来维持和平，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.84,0:41:08.00,English,,0,0,0,,So there's a lot of looting. So the entire country broke down.\N{\rChinese}于是大规模掠夺，整个国家陷入混乱。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.20,0:41:10.68,English,,0,0,0,,Second thing is that during the air campaign,\N{\rChinese}第二件事是，在空袭期间，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.04,0:41:15.80,English,,0,0,0,,America, America destroyed all the infrastructure necessary for society, okay?\N{\rChinese}美国，美国把社会所需的所有基础设施都摧毁了，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.90,0:41:18.88,English,,0,0,0,,So including water supply, including electricity grid.\N{\rChinese}包括供水、包括电网。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.46,0:41:21.58,English,,0,0,0,,Why would you do that if your intention was to\N{\rChinese}如果你的意图是……
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.14,0:41:23.64,English,,0,0,0,,bring democracy to the country, right?\N{\rChinese}把民主带到这个国家，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.22,0:41:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,The third thing is that the very first thing the American government did\N{\rChinese}第三件事是，当美国政府第一次接管伊拉克时，做的第一件事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.02,0:41:32.58,English,,0,0,0,,when they took control over Iraq is something called de -bafflication,\N{\rChinese}那件事叫做去中心化（de‑bafflication）
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.68,0:41:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,okay? Which is to say that if you used to work for the old government,\N{\rChinese}好的？也就是说，如果你以前为旧政府工作，现在就失业了。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.62,0:41:39.30,English,,0,0,0,,you're now out of a job.\N{\rChinese}嘿，伊拉克军队现在不再为你工作。
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.82,0:41:42.02,English,,0,0,0,,Hey, the Iraqi military, they're not going to work for you.\N{\rChinese}Hey, the Iraqi military, they're not going to work for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.02,0:41:45.10,English,,0,0,0,,You're now disbanded. And\N{\rChinese}你现在解散了。然后，问题是，呃，
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.10,0:41:46.66,English,,0,0,0,,then the question then is, ha,\N{\rChinese}如果你的最终目标是把民主带到这个国家，…
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.94,0:41:51.56,English,,0,0,0,,if your ultimate objective is to bring democracy to the country,\N{\rChinese}if your ultimate objective is tobring democracy to the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.70,0:41:53.12,English,,0,0,0,,why would you destroy\N{\rChinese}为什么你要毁掉国家的政治基础设施？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.66,0:41:56.32,English,,0,0,0,,all political infrastructure in the country?\N{\rChinese}为什么你要毁掉国家自我治理的能力以及维持秩序？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.02,0:42:01.16,English,,0,0,0,,Why would you destroy the ability for the country to govern itself as well as to maintain order,\N{\rChinese}为什么你要毁掉国家自我治理的能力以及维持秩序？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.36,0:42:02.86,English,,0,0,0,,as well as to feed the population?\N{\rChinese}也为了给人们提供食物？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.06,0:42:04.26,English,,0,0,0,,Why would you do that? Okay?\N{\rChinese}那你为什么要这么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.40,0:42:06.76,English,,0,0,0,,So an argument can be made that the real intention\N{\rChinese}于是可以说真正的意图是…
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.30,0:42:11.16,English,,0,0,0,,was not to bring democracy to Iraq, it was just to destroy Iraq, to maintain American,\N{\rChinese}它不是把民主带到伊拉克，而是要把伊拉克摧毁，保持美国的霸权，并给别人上一课。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.02,0:42:16.60,English,,0,0,0,,to maintain supremacy as well as to teach others a lesson.\N{\rChinese}别惹我们，我们会来摧毁你，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.72,0:42:18.34,English,,0,0,0,,Don't mess with us, we'll come and destroy you, okay?\N{\rChinese}Don't mess with us, we'llcome and destroy you, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.40,0:42:22.48,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Okay,\N{\rChinese}这有道理吗？好吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.58,0:42:25.20,English,,0,0,0,,but this is something we will discuss later on, okay?\N{\rChinese}但这点我们稍后再说，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.28,0:42:27.30,English,,0,0,0,,In another class, okay? All right.\N{\rChinese}在另一节课里，好吧，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.32,0:42:30.52,English,,0,0,0,,All right, let's now move to the last topic,\N{\rChinese}好的，接下来我们进入最后一个话题，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.98,0:42:34.46,English,,0,0,0,,which is the theory of empire. So\N{\rChinese}就是帝国理论。于是
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.46,0:42:37.12,English,,0,0,0,,this is not the first theory of empire America had.\N{\rChinese}这并不是美国第一个帝国理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.30,0:42:38.62,English,,0,0,0,,It's actually the second theory of empire.\N{\rChinese}它实际上是第二个帝国理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.06,0:42:43.54,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The first theory of empire was in 1991.\N{\rChinese}好？第一个帝国理论是在1991年。
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.38,0:42:46.80,English,,0,0,0,,Remember that in 1991,\N{\rChinese}记得1991年，
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.16,0:42:50.20,English,,0,0,0,,America launched\N{\rChinese}美国发动
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.66,0:42:54.36,English,,0,0,0,,an attack against Saddam Hussein because\N{\rChinese}对萨达姆·侯赛因的攻击，因为
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.36,0:42:56.96,English,,0,0,0,,Saddam Hussein invaded Kuwait, right?\N{\rChinese}萨达姆·侯赛因入侵科威特，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.60,0:43:01.92,English,,0,0,0,,So at that time, 1991,\N{\rChinese}于是到了1991年，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.42,0:43:03.68,English,,0,0,0,,the Soviet Union had collapsed.\N{\rChinese}苏联已经解体。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.02,0:43:07.06,English,,0,0,0,,America was the only hegemon, was the only power,\N{\rChinese}美国则是唯一的霸权，唯一的强国。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.22,0:43:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,and it presented a new theory of empire, right?\N{\rChinese}并且提出了新的帝国理论，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.24,0:43:12.12,English,,0,0,0,,How America will rule the world, okay?\N{\rChinese}美国将如何统治世界，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.73,0:43:14.32,English,,0,0,0,,So the first idea is\N{\rChinese}于是第一个想法是
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.32,0:43:18.68,English,,0,0,0,,limited strategic\N{\rChinese}有限的战略目标或目标，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.68,0:43:22.66,English,,0,0,0,,goals or objectives, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是比如说，2003年时…
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.35,0:43:26.58,English,,0,0,0,,So for example, in 2003 when\N{\rChinese}So for example,in 2003 when
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.58,0:43:28.62,English,,0,0,0,,America invaded Iraq,\N{\rChinese}美国入侵伊拉克，
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.96,0:43:30.42,English,,0,0,0,,its strategic goals\N{\rChinese}其战略目标
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.42,0:43:35.20,English,,0,0,0,,were pretty unachievable, okay?\N{\rChinese}相当可达不到，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.38,0:43:38.04,English,,0,0,0,,It was basically like we're gonna bring democracy and\N{\rChinese}它基本上就是我们要把民主和和平带到伊拉克和中东
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.04,0:43:40.94,English,,0,0,0,,peace to Iraq and the Middle East, okay?\N{\rChinese}而在由父亲领导的波斯特海湾战争中，...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.16,0:43:44.98,English,,0,0,0,,Whereas in the Persian Gulf War, led by the father,\N{\rChinese}Whereas in the Persian Gulf War, led by the father,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.04,0:43:48.74,English,,0,0,0,,right, George Herbert Walker Bush, the first\N{\rChinese}对，乔治·赫伯特·沃克·布什，首要且唯一的目标是把萨达姆·侯赛因从科威特赶走。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.74,0:43:53.86,English,,0,0,0,,and only goal was to remove Saddam Hussein from Kuwait.\N{\rChinese}就是这样，行吗？我们不去伊拉克把萨达姆·侯赛因推倒。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.08,0:43:57.66,English,,0,0,0,,That's it, okay? We're not gonna go to Iraq and topple Saddam Hussein.\N{\rChinese}就是这么简单，行吗？我们不去伊拉克推倒萨达姆·侯赛因。
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.88,0:44:00.34,English,,0,0,0,,We're not gonna inflict punishment on Saddam Hussein.\N{\rChinese}我们不打算给萨达姆·侯赛因加重罚。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.48,0:44:04.20,English,,0,0,0,,All we wanna do is remove him from Kuwait, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们要做的就是把他从科威特赶走，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.28,0:44:08.38,English,,0,0,0,,That's the first thing. Second thing is that, okay, we're gonna have to do this.\N{\rChinese}第一件事是这样，第二件事是我们要去做这件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.62,0:44:11.58,English,,0,0,0,,We're gonna have to do this. America did so\N{\rChinese}我们要去做这件事。美国就是这么做的
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.58,0:44:15.00,English,,0,0,0,,with a coalition of countries, okay?\N{\rChinese}与一支由各国组成的联盟一起，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.38,0:44:19.14,English,,0,0,0,,Dozens of other countries were part of the war,\N{\rChinese}数十个其他国家也参与了这场战争
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.28,0:44:23.98,English,,0,0,0,,and America played a leading role, but it also had to defer to its partners, okay?\N{\rChinese}美国扮演了主导角色，但也得向伙伴们让步，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.48,0:44:28.56,English,,0,0,0,,So for example, countries like Saudi Arabia,\N{\rChinese}比如说，像沙特阿拉伯这样的国家，
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.06,0:44:32.66,English,,0,0,0,,who participated in the war, were like, there's no way we'll topple Saddam Hussein.\N{\rChinese}他们参与了战争，结果就是没办法把萨达姆·侯赛因推倒。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.86,0:44:34.72,English,,0,0,0,,We'll only stop at Kuwait, okay?\N{\rChinese}我们只会停在科威特，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.12,0:44:37.88,English,,0,0,0,,So the United States deferred to its partners, okay?\N{\rChinese}于是美国向伙伴们让步，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.42,0:44:40.52,English,,0,0,0,,And the third thing was,\N{\rChinese}第三点是……
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.08,0:44:42.86,English,,0,0,0,,and this is the most important is that\N{\rChinese}并且最重要的是
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.24,0:44:47.98,English,,0,0,0,,the ultimate leader was the United Nations.\N{\rChinese}最终的主导者是联合国。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.34,0:44:52.76,English,,0,0,0,,The United States had to go and make a case to the United Nations.\N{\rChinese}美国必须去向联合国阐述理由。
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.90,0:44:55.76,English,,0,0,0,,The United Nations gave its consent\N{\rChinese}联合国已批准
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.14,0:44:59.64,English,,0,0,0,,to the military action, okay? So the United States made the argument\N{\rChinese}军行动，行吗？于是美国作了论证
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.64,0:45:01.60,English,,0,0,0,,that this is not a U.S.\N{\rChinese}这不是美国的行动
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.84,0:45:03.80,English,,0,0,0,,military action. It is a U.N.\N{\rChinese}军事行动。它是联合国的行动。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.92,0:45:05.40,English,,0,0,0,,military action, okay?\N{\rChinese}军事行动，好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.92,0:45:07.68,English,,0,0,0,,And so the important principle is to,\N{\rChinese}而且重要的原则是……
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.72,0:45:14.02,English,,0,0,0,,maintain the rules based in national order.\N{\rChinese}保持基于民族国家的规则。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.50,0:45:18.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So what America said at\N{\rChinese}好吗？于是美国在……说的就是……
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.76,0:45:23.46,English,,0,0,0,,that point is, yeah, I know we are the greatest power in the world.\N{\rChinese}那一点是，嗯，我知道我们是世界上最大的力量。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.56,0:45:25.18,English,,0,0,0,,I know the Soviet Union has collapsed.\N{\rChinese}我知道苏联已经解体。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.48,0:45:28.02,English,,0,0,0,,I know that militarily no one can challenge us.\N{\rChinese}我知道在军事上没有人能挑战我们。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.32,0:45:31.66,English,,0,0,0,,But with this power comes great responsibility.\N{\rChinese}但拥有这份力量也带来大责任。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.90,0:45:33.80,English,,0,0,0,,We must show humility.\N{\rChinese}我们必须表现谦逊。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.18,0:45:35.78,English,,0,0,0,,We must show discipline.\N{\rChinese}我们必须表现纪律。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.78,0:45:37.34,English,,0,0,0,,We must show restraint.\N{\rChinese}我们必须表现克制。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.08,0:45:43.52,English,,0,0,0,,Our priority will be to maintain the national rules based order\N{\rChinese}我们的首要任务是保持以国家规则为基础的秩序
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.52,0:45:46.94,English,,0,0,0,,because this will bring prosperity, freedom,\N{\rChinese}因为这将带来繁荣与自由
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.10,0:45:48.92,English,,0,0,0,,and stability to everyone.\N{\rChinese}并为大家带来稳定。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.30,0:45:52.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And that means that\N{\rChinese}好的？这就意味着……
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.26,0:45:54.32,English,,0,0,0,,if we use the military,\N{\rChinese}如果我们动用军力，
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.54,0:45:58.92,English,,0,0,0,,it will only because it's the last resort,\N{\rChinese}它只会在最后手段时才使用。
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.10,0:46:02.80,English,,0,0,0,,the last option, and only for a limited strategic objective.\N{\rChinese}最后的手段，仅为有限的战略目标。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.66,0:46:07.02,English,,0,0,0,,We will only do this if we do so with partners.\N{\rChinese}我们只有在与伙伴一起行动时才会这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.12,0:46:09.94,English,,0,0,0,,And we will only do so\N{\rChinese}我们只会在联合国授权的伞下这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.94,0:46:13.14,English,,0,0,0,,under the umbrella of UN authority.\N{\rChinese}我们只会在联合国授权的伞下这么做。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.84,0:46:16.46,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So this is the first theory of empire.\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是第一种帝国理论。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.84,0:46:19.62,English,,0,0,0,,When you think about it, wow, great!\N{\rChinese}当你想到它时，哇，太棒了！
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.80,0:46:22.78,English,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful world, right?\N{\rChinese}多么美好的世界，吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.30,0:46:28.88,English,,0,0,0,,Here's a question then. Why did America\N{\rChinese}接下来是个问题。为什么美国……
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.96,0:46:36.78,English,,0,0,0,,not do this anymore? Why did they switch to shock and awe?\N{\rChinese}他们为什么不再这样做？为什么转而为震撼与惊叹？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.02,0:46:41.14,English,,0,0,0,,Shock and awe is basically unlimited strategic goals,\N{\rChinese}震撼与惊叹基本上是无限的战略目标，单边军事行动，对吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.46,0:46:43.94,English,,0,0,0,,unilateral military action, right?\N{\rChinese}我们，美国，自己来做这件事。不需要别人。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.06,0:46:45.86,English,,0,0,0,,We, America, will do this by ourselves. We don't need anyone.\N{\rChinese}We, America, will do this by ourselves. We don't need anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.96,0:46:49.70,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And America is just basically bullying.\N{\rChinese}好的？美国就是在霸凌。
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.94,0:46:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,We make the rules. Why did America do this?\N{\rChinese}我们制定规则。为什么美国会这么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.06,0:46:58.24,English,,0,0,0,,Why this transition from the first theory of empire, which\N{\rChinese}为什么从第一种帝国理论过渡到第二种？
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.24,0:47:00.88,English,,0,0,0,,is great, it would allow America to rule the world forever,\N{\rChinese}它很棒，可以让美国永远统治世界，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.16,0:47:05.70,English,,0,0,0,,to now the second theory of empire, which is pissing the entire world off?\N{\rChinese}现在是第二种帝国理论，正把全世界搞得一团糟？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.78,0:47:16.68,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Okay. So this is really hard to understand, okay?\N{\rChinese}为什么？好吧，这个很难懂，懂吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.86,0:47:18.64,English,,0,0,0,,But let's use an analogy, okay?\N{\rChinese}好吧，先用个比喻来说明，行吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.80,0:47:20.48,English,,0,0,0,,So Jack is my son.\N{\rChinese}于是杰克是我的儿子。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.68,0:47:22.98,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And I'm a billionaire.\N{\rChinese}我是一位亿万富翁。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.60,0:47:24.86,English,,0,0,0,,I have $10 billion.\N{\rChinese}我有100亿美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.00,0:47:30.26,English,,0,0,0,,Why do I have $10 billion? It's because one, I'm smart.\N{\rChinese}我之所以有100亿美元？因为一，我很聪明。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.44,0:47:34.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? I'm smarter than everyone else. Two, I work really hard.\N{\rChinese}我很聪明，二，我很努力。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.52,0:47:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And three, I bribe a lot of politicians.\N{\rChinese}好的？三，我给很多政客送礼。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.86,0:47:41.78,English,,0,0,0,,So I have $10 billion. But I'm like 95 years old.\N{\rChinese}于是我有100亿美元。可我已95岁。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.00,0:47:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,And I know I'm going to die.\N{\rChinese}我知道自己会去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.46,0:47:47.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So I invite Jack, who's my son, to dinner.\N{\rChinese}好的？于是我邀请我的儿子杰克来吃饭。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.38,0:47:50.48,English,,0,0,0,,And I say to Jack, Jack,\N{\rChinese}我对杰克说，杰克，
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.48,0:47:54.00,English,,0,0,0,,I love you and I want what's best for you.\N{\rChinese}我爱你，想让你过得更好。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.80,0:47:57.62,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to die very soon, and you will inherit my empire.\N{\rChinese}我很快就要去世了，你将继承我的帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.26,0:48:02.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And I want you to know\N{\rChinese}好的吗？我想让你知道
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.40,0:48:05.68,English,,0,0,0,,that you don't have to worry about anything,\N{\rChinese}你不必为任何事担忧。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.90,0:48:08.86,English,,0,0,0,,Jack, because I have 100 advisors who\N{\rChinese}杰克，因为我有100位顾问在掌控这帝国，管理这帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.86,0:48:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,control this empire, who manage this empire.\N{\rChinese}他们很出色。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.64,0:48:12.84,English,,0,0,0,,And they are great.\N{\rChinese}And they are great.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.12,0:48:15.20,English,,0,0,0,,They're experienced. They're loyal.\N{\rChinese}他们经验丰富，忠诚可靠。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.24,0:48:20.46,English,,0,0,0,,They're strategic. Every year, Jack,\N{\rChinese}他们具备战略眼光，每年，杰克，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.26,0:48:23.98,English,,0,0,0,,they make 10% for us.\N{\rChinese}他们每年为我们赚取10%。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.10,0:48:27.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So $10 billion to make $1 billion for us every year.\N{\rChinese}好的？所以每年投入100亿美元，能为我们赚取10亿美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.64,0:48:32.96,English,,0,0,0,,When I go, they're still going to manage this empire for us.\N{\rChinese}我去的时候，他们仍会为我们管理这帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.26,0:48:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,And you know what? They're going to give you, every year, Jack,\N{\rChinese}你知道吗？他们每年都会给你，杰克，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.80,0:48:40.62,English,,0,0,0,,$100 million. You can do whatever you want.\N{\rChinese}$1亿。你可以随便干什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.82,0:48:42.04,English,,0,0,0,,You want to go buy an airplane?\N{\rChinese}你想去买一架飞机？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.30,0:48:43.98,English,,0,0,0,,Do that. You want to go buy an island?\N{\rChinese}去吧。你想去买一座岛屿？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.06,0:48:46.52,English,,0,0,0,,Do that. You want to party with movie stars?\N{\rChinese}去吧。你想跟电影明星一起玩吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.10,0:48:48.74,English,,0,0,0,,Do that. You can do whatever you want.\N{\rChinese}去吧。你可以随便干什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.32,0:48:52.88,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的吗？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.88,0:48:56.16,English,,0,0,0,,Jack, as my last wish,\N{\rChinese}杰克，作为我的最后愿望，
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.72,0:49:00.94,English,,0,0,0,,as my dying wish, I want you, Jack, my son, who I love,\N{\rChinese}作为我临终的愿望，我想让你，杰克，我的儿子，我所爱的人，
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.84,0:49:03.32,English,,0,0,0,,to promise me\N{\rChinese}向我许诺
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.22,0:49:08.46,English,,0,0,0,,that after I die, you will listen to my 100 advisors.\N{\rChinese}我去世后，你会听从我的一百位顾问。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.62,0:49:12.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, Jack, do you promise me?\N{\rChinese}好吗？所以，杰克，你答应我吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.82,0:49:17.86,English,,0,0,0,,You promise me, right? And then, I die.\N{\rChinese}你答应我，对吧？然后，我去世。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.08,0:49:21.38,English,,0,0,0,,And then what is the first thing that Jack will do?\N{\rChinese}那接下来杰克会先做什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.20,0:49:23.70,English,,0,0,0,,The very first thing that Jack will do is the first thing he will do.\N{\rChinese}杰克先做的第一件事，就是他要做的第一件事。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.86,0:49:31.10,English,,0,0,0,,Come on, guys. It's not hard. Your first thing you will do,\N{\rChinese}来吧，伙计们。没那么难。你们先要做的事是……
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.14,0:49:33.22,English,,0,0,0,,okay, is fire everyone.\N{\rChinese}好的，大家点火。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.94,0:49:35.24,English,,0,0,0,,Get out of here. Okay?\N{\rChinese}离开这里。好吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.64,0:49:40.82,English,,0,0,0,,What's the second thing you will do? You're going to hire all your friends,\N{\rChinese}第二件事你会做什么？你会雇佣所有朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.94,0:49:42.60,English,,0,0,0,,Jack. Okay? You're going to hire all your friends.\N{\rChinese}杰克。好吧？你会雇佣所有朋友。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.68,0:49:45.26,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And what's the third thing you're going to do?\N{\rChinese}好吧？接下来你要做的第三件事是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.80,0:49:49.26,English,,0,0,0,,You're going to do something really stupid.\N{\rChinese}你要做的事会很傻哦。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.40,0:49:50.68,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You'll be like, you know what?\N{\rChinese}好的？你会说，知道吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.68,0:49:53.86,English,,0,0,0,,My dad only made $10 billion.\N{\rChinese}我爸只赚了100亿美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.42,0:49:56.62,English,,0,0,0,,Those advisors only make 10% a year.\N{\rChinese}那些顾问每年只赚10%。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.04,0:49:58.74,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to invest in Bitcoin.\N{\rChinese}我打算投资比特币。
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.66,0:50:01.26,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to invest in AI.\N{\rChinese}我打算投资人工智能。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.96,0:50:05.14,English,,0,0,0,,I'm going to invest in the Chinese stock market, the Chinese real estate market,\N{\rChinese}我打算投资中国股市和中国房市。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.26,0:50:06.88,English,,0,0,0,,and make $100 billion.\N{\rChinese}并赚到1000亿美元。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.28,0:50:09.84,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And then he loses all the money.\N{\rChinese}好？然后他把钱全失去。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.98,0:50:12.58,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? All right?\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？好了？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.00,0:50:16.98,English,,0,0,0,,This happens all the time, guys.\N{\rChinese}这件事一直在发生，伙计们。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.04,0:50:18.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Right?\N{\rChinese}好？对吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.06,0:50:21.82,English,,0,0,0,,Ask yourself, if your dad were rich\N{\rChinese}问问自己，如果你爸爸很富有的话。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:21.82,0:50:24.42,English,,0,0,0,,and he was about to leave you a lot of money,\N{\rChinese}他刚好要给你留下一大笔钱，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.54,0:50:27.78,English,,0,0,0,,would you listen to professional people?\N{\rChinese}你会听专业人士的建议吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.98,0:50:30.38,English,,0,0,0,,No. No. You'd be like, no, I want to have fun.\N{\rChinese}不。你会说：不，我想玩玩。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.48,0:50:32.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So the question then is,\N{\rChinese}好的？那问题是，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.36,0:50:34.88,English,,0,0,0,,the first fear of empire,\N{\rChinese}帝国的第一种恐惧，
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.76,0:50:38.62,English,,0,0,0,,okay, which said\N{\rChinese}好的，正如所说。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.62,0:50:41.12,English,,0,0,0,,that for America to maintain its empire,\N{\rChinese}为美国维持其帝国，需要向世界展示谦逊、纪律与克制。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.30,0:50:44.18,English,,0,0,0,,it must demonstrate to the world humility,\N{\rChinese}为美国维持其帝国，需要向世界展示谦逊、纪律与克制。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.06,0:50:46.84,English,,0,0,0,,discipline, and restraint.\N{\rChinese}为美国维持其帝国，需要向世界展示谦逊、纪律与克制。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.68,0:50:50.64,English,,0,0,0,,Why did they get rid of this and move to shock and\N{\rChinese}为什么他们把这件事抛开，转而用震撼和惊叹来表达？
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.64,0:50:53.58,English,,0,0,0,,awe, which is like, we'll do anything we want.\N{\rChinese}震撼和惊叹，意思是我们可以随心所欲地做任何事。
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.92,0:51:01.34,English,,0,0,0,,Why? Why? Why would they do that?\N{\rChinese}为什么？为什么？他们为什么要这么做？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.24,0:51:07.56,English,,0,0,0,,Because it's fun. Okay? Do you understand?\N{\rChinese}因为很有趣。好吗？你明白了吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.42,0:51:11.94,English,,0,0,0,,What is the point of having an empire if\N{\rChinese}拥有帝国的意义是什么，如果你不能无缘无故地把东西炸掉？
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.94,0:51:14.82,English,,0,0,0,,you cannot blow things up for no reason?\N{\rChinese}you cannot blow things up for no reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.82,0:51:19.38,English,,0,0,0,,There's no point. We have the greatest military in the world.\N{\rChinese}没有意义。我们拥有世界上最强大的军队。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.52,0:51:21.22,English,,0,0,0,,Let's just blow things up for like no reason.\N{\rChinese}就把东西炸掉吧，随便用。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.34,0:51:25.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? All right? Now,\N{\rChinese}好了？行吗？现在，
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.94,0:51:30.92,English,,0,0,0,,there are three fundamental problems with shock and awe.\N{\rChinese}有三大基本问题与震撼与惊叹相关。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.84,0:51:35.02,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The first problem is that\N{\rChinese}好了？第一个问题是……
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.90,0:51:38.28,English,,0,0,0,,you become over committed.\N{\rChinese}你会过度投入。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.46,0:51:44.14,English,,0,0,0,,Do you understand? You believe that shock and awe allows you to be God.\N{\rChinese}你明白了吗？你认为震撼与惊叹能让你成神。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.34,0:51:46.62,English,,0,0,0,,You can be anywhere at once fighting all wars.\N{\rChinese}你可以瞬间到任何地方，打一场所有战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.62,0:51:48.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You're over committed.\N{\rChinese}好了？你已经过度投入。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.66,0:51:52.56,English,,0,0,0,,Second is, you lack strategic focus.\N{\rChinese}第二点是，你缺乏战略焦点。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.10,0:51:58.04,English,,0,0,0,,Meaning that, you actually don't have a plan.\N{\rChinese}也就是说，你实际上没有计划。
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.50,0:52:00.58,English,,0,0,0,,You don't know what you want to do with this empire.\N{\rChinese}你不知道用这个帝国想做什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.92,0:52:02.62,English,,0,0,0,,You know you just want to maintain this empire.\N{\rChinese}你知道你只是想维持这个帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.86,0:52:05.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So you don't actually have a strategy in place.\N{\rChinese}好了？所以你实际上没有具体的战略。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.32,0:52:08.76,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the third thing is,\N{\rChinese}第三点是，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.34,0:52:15.94,English,,0,0,0,,hubris. You don't think anyone can challenge you.\N{\rChinese}自大傲。你以为无人能挑战你。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.94,0:52:18.30,English,,0,0,0,,You don't think you can lose a war.\N{\rChinese}你以为自己不可能输一场战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.32,0:52:23.20,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And so, the idea of hubris is this.\N{\rChinese}好了？于是，傲的概念就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.68,0:52:26.58,English,,0,0,0,,Right now, America has this huge empire.\N{\rChinese}现在，美国拥有庞大的帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.88,0:52:31.56,English,,0,0,0,,And it's refusing to spend the necessary resources to protect the empire.\N{\rChinese}它却不愿投入必要资源来保卫帝国。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.88,0:52:33.38,English,,0,0,0,,So for example, the US Navy. Okay?\N{\rChinese}比如说，美国海军。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.58,0:52:37.36,English,,0,0,0,,In 1945, it had 7,600 ships.\N{\rChinese}1945年，它拥有7600艘船。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.72,0:52:39.08,English,,0,0,0,,Today, guess what guys?\N{\rChinese}今天，猜猜是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.38,0:52:41.42,English,,0,0,0,,That's 475.\N{\rChinese}就是475艘。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.62,0:52:46.98,English,,0,0,0,,These 475 ships must go around all around the world to protect shipping lanes.\N{\rChinese}这些475艘船必须环绕世界各地，守护航运通道。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.24,0:52:51.10,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The US military,\N{\rChinese}好的？美国军队，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.24,0:52:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,in 1991, during the first Persian Gulf War,\N{\rChinese}1991年，第一次波斯湾战争期间，
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.44,0:52:56.10,English,,0,0,0,,had 2 million soldiers.\N{\rChinese}拥有200万士兵。
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.42,0:52:59.52,English,,0,0,0,,Today, it has 1.3 million soldiers.\N{\rChinese}今天有130万士兵。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.60,0:53:03.34,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, in other words,\N{\rChinese}好吧？换句话说，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.64,0:53:08.10,English,,0,0,0,,if America ever fights a war, a major war, it's going to have a lot of problems.\N{\rChinese}如果美国真的打起一场大战，它将面临许多问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.98,0:53:13.18,English,,0,0,0,,The other thing is that America doesn't even have manufacturing capacity anymore.\N{\rChinese}另外，美国现在甚至没有制造能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.32,0:53:15.08,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? It doesn't have any factories anymore.\N{\rChinese}好吧？它已经没有任何工厂了。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.24,0:53:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, Which means that if it fights a war, it can't fight a war for a very long time.\N{\rChinese}好吧？也就是说，如果它打仗，它就不能持续很久。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.90,0:53:21.34,English,,0,0,0,,So, the example is that\N{\rChinese}所以，例子是：
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.18,0:53:24.50,English,,0,0,0,,for every ship that America makes,\N{\rChinese}每造一艘船，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.14,0:53:27.60,English,,0,0,0,,China can make 300 ships.\N{\rChinese}中国可以造300艘船。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.02,0:53:32.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? America no longer has this manufacturing capacity that\N{\rChinese}好吧？美国不再拥有二战时期的制造能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.30,0:53:34.28,English,,0,0,0,,it had during World War II.\N{\rChinese}好吧？美国不再拥有二战时期的制造能力。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.46,0:53:36.18,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So, in other words,\N{\rChinese}好吧？换句话说，
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.42,0:53:43.30,English,,0,0,0,,why will the military agree to the stupid war in Iran?\N{\rChinese}为什么军方会同意在伊朗搞这场愚蠢的战争？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.70,0:53:45.12,English,,0,0,0,,Because it's over committed.\N{\rChinese}因为它过度投入。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.12,0:53:47.88,English,,0,0,0,,It has no strategy. And it's because it's arrogant.\N{\rChinese}它没有策略，正因为它自负自傲。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.18,0:53:51.94,English,,0,0,0,,All right? And the military is like this\N{\rChinese}好的？军方就是这么说的。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.94,0:53:54.58,English,,0,0,0,,because of what happened in 2003, shock and awe.\N{\rChinese}因为2003年的事，震撼与敬畏。
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.86,0:53:57.96,English,,0,0,0,,It doesn't make sense to you guys. All right?\N{\rChinese}这句话对你们来说没道理。好吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.98,0:54:01.48,English,,0,0,0,,So, next class, we will look at what the Iran war will look like.\N{\rChinese}那么，下节课我们将看看伊朗战争会是什么样子。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.58,0:54:04.58,English,,0,0,0,,And I guarantee you that shock\N{\rChinese}我向你保证这点震撼
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.58,0:54:06.70,English,,0,0,0,,and awe is not going to work in Iran.\N{\rChinese}而敬畏在伊朗也没用。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.16,0:54:09.76,English,,0,0,0,,All right? But I'll explain why.\N{\rChinese}好吧？我来解释一下原因。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.94,0:54:12.72,English,,0,0,0,,Next class. Any questions before we end for the day?\N{\rChinese}下节课。今天结束前还有问题吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.20,0:54:19.66,English,,0,0,0,,Okay. I'm going to go to the next class. So, what's the difference between the analogy between the theory of the first theory\N{\rChinese}好的。我准备进入下一节课。那第一理论与第二理论的类比有什么区别？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.66,0:54:23.62,English,,0,0,0,,and the theory of the second theory? Oh, so, Celine asked a great question.\N{\rChinese}哦，塞琳提了个好问题。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.38,0:54:27.62,English,,0,0,0,,What's the difference between the people\N{\rChinese}第一类人和第二类人有什么区别？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.62,0:54:30.14,English,,0,0,0,,who believe in the first theory and the second theory?\N{\rChinese}两类人分别相信哪种理论？
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.24,0:54:32.30,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Okay. And the answer is this.\N{\rChinese}好的？好的。答案就是这样。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.42,0:54:36.38,English,,0,0,0,,The people who believe in the first theory came from an older generation.\N{\rChinese}相信第一理论的人来自上一代。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.68,0:54:39.52,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? This is the generation that fought in World War II\N{\rChinese}好的？这就是二战与冷战的那一代人
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.52,0:54:42.10,English,,0,0,0,,and who fought the Cold War.\N{\rChinese}他们曾在二战中战斗过，并在冷战中作战
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.94,0:54:45.76,English,,0,0,0,,So, they understand what war looks like.\N{\rChinese}于是，他们懂得战争的样子。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.86,0:54:49.16,English,,0,0,0,,War is really bloody\N{\rChinese}战争真的很血腥。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.16,0:54:51.16,English,,0,0,0,,and it's terrible.\N{\rChinese}而且很糟。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.68,0:54:54.02,English,,0,0,0,,And we must do our best to avoid war.\N{\rChinese}我们要尽力避免战争。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.30,0:54:57.00,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? The second generation, 2003,\N{\rChinese}好的？第二代，2003。
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.44,0:55:00.90,English,,0,0,0,,are individuals who don't know what war is.\N{\rChinese}是指那些不知道战争是什么的人。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.54,0:55:05.28,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Like, if you actually look at videos from 2003,\N{\rChinese}好吧？比如说你真的去看2003年的视频，战争其实就像一场视频游戏。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.50,0:55:07.50,English,,0,0,0,,the war, it actually looks like a video game.\N{\rChinese}它看起来就像一场视频游戏。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.90,0:55:13.14,English,,0,0,0,,You understand? You don't actually see what they saw in Vietnam.\N{\rChinese}你明白吗？你并没有真正看到越南时他们所见的情景。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.14,0:55:18.40,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? And the third generation, which was all these soldiers losing their arms\N{\rChinese}好吧？第三代，那些士兵失去双臂、哭泣的画面。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.40,0:55:22.56,English,,0,0,0,,and crying. Okay? I mean, the images from Vietnam were just terrible.\N{\rChinese}我说，越南的影像真是糟透了。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.64,0:55:25.08,English,,0,0,0,,It was hard for people to watch.\N{\rChinese}观看起来很难。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.32,0:55:28.66,English,,0,0,0,,But, the Gulf War in 2003, it was just a video game.\N{\rChinese}但2003年的海湾战争就像一场视频游戏。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.74,0:55:30.22,English,,0,0,0,,It was just like things getting blown up.\N{\rChinese}就像一切都在爆炸一样。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.30,0:55:31.64,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? You don't actually see the people dying.\N{\rChinese}好的？你并没有真正看到人们死亡的情景。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.90,0:55:34.00,English,,0,0,0,,And again, only 20 people died,\N{\rChinese}再说一次，只有20人死亡，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.20,0:55:38.40,English,,0,0,0,,20 soldiers died in 2003.\N{\rChinese}2003年有20名士兵死亡。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.14,0:55:41.74,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? So,\N{\rChinese}好的？所以，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.70,0:55:45.08,English,,0,0,0,,um, in other words, unfortunately,\N{\rChinese}呃，换句话说，没想到，
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.48,0:55:48.08,English,,0,0,0,,America is headed towards disaster.\N{\rChinese}美国正走向灾难。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.46,0:55:52.22,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? Because the people in charge have no experience.\N{\rChinese}好的？因为掌权者没有经验。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.60,0:55:54.10,English,,0,0,0,,They don't know what war is.\N{\rChinese}他们不知道战争是什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.36,0:55:57.34,English,,0,0,0,,And they don't know what the horse of war is.\N{\rChinese}他们也不知道战争的马是什么。
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.36,0:55:59.94,English,,0,0,0,,And they've inherited a lot of money.\N{\rChinese}他们继承了大量财富。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.26,0:56:03.00,English,,0,0,0,,And they want to enjoy the money.\N{\rChinese}他们想要享受这笔钱。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.10,0:56:04.56,English,,0,0,0,,Okay? They want to have fun. Okay?\N{\rChinese}他们想玩得开心。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.66,0:56:06.20,English,,0,0,0,,Does that make sense? Okay.\N{\rChinese}那有道理吗？好吧。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.26,0:56:07.70,English,,0,0,0,,All right. Great. So, I'll see you guys next class.\N{\rChinese}好的。太好了。那我下节课见你们。
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.24,0:56:10.62,English,,0,0,0,,Bye. Bye. Bye. Bye.\N{\rChinese}再见。再见。再见。再见。
